channel.title: Chrome error 138
channel.description:
[img]http://img406.imageshack.us/img406/1397/err138.png[/img]
I get that when I try to visit a lot of sites... Does anyone know why? It's not just for Google Chrome, either, so don't suggest another browser. Does my ISP block this shit? It's not any anti-virus software that blocks it, because it does this for all computers on my network whether they have an anti-virus installed or not. The only way I can visit the 'blocked' sites is by using Tor.
